Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubens Heimkehr der Diana (Slg. Neger)" addressed (inside) to "Prof H G Evers 43 Waldstrasse Traisa bei Darmstadt Germany"

- Extracts from different publications
- Bibliographic reference
- Notes about Rubens' Diana in Kassel
- Journal: "The Bulletin of the Cleveland Museum of art for February 1960"

The inventory of 1993 also mentions reproductions, but these are missing and were probably taken out in the Rubenianum and filed in the Rubens documentation.
